roke, S2 finals with a time of 1:00.33, becoming the first Singaporean to win multiple gold medals at the Paralympics.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chew |first1=Joan |title=Paralympics: Yip Pin Xiu wins 2nd gold at Rio Games, says 'words cannot describe how I feel now' |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/paralympics-history-maker-yip-pin-xiu-wins-gold-in-womens-50m-backstroke-s2-second-title-of |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=8 December 2019 |date=16 September 2016}}</ref> On 12 September, swimmer [[Theresa Goh]] won a bronze medal in the SB4 100m breaststroke final, with a time of 1:55.55.<ref name=16Para100mbreastFinals>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/sport/paralympics-singapore-s-theresa-goh-wins-bronze-in-100m-breastst-7788098|title=Paralympics: Singapore's Theresa Goh wins bronze in 100m breaststroke SB4 final|website=Channel NewsAsia}}</ref> While qualifying for the finals, she set a new Asian record in the heats at 1:54.50.<ref name=16Para100mbreastHeats>{{cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/sports/theresa-goh-sets-new-asian-mark-en-route-reaching-breaststroke-final|title=Theresa Goh sets new Asian mark en route to reaching breaststroke final|website=TODAYonline}}</ref>\n*8 September \u2013 Plans for a new HDB town in [[Tengah, Singapore|Tengah]] are launched. It will be a town in a forest with a car-free town centre.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cheng |first1=Kenneth |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/peek-tengah-next-new-hdb-town-size-bishan |title=A peek into Tengah, the next new HDB town the size of Bishan |website=Today |access-date=28 April 2019 |date=8 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Heng |first1=Janice |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/housing/tengah-the-first-hdb-town-since-punggol-to-have-forest-fringe-car-free-town-centre |title=Tengah, the first HDB town since Punggol, to have forest fringe, car-free town centre |website=The Straits Times |access-date=6 November 2019 |date=8 September 2016}}</re