 fire on Changi Airport runway; no injuries reported | date=27 June 2016 | last2=Kaur | website=The Straits Times}}</ref>\n* 30 June \u2013 \n**[[Funan DigitaLife Mall]] ceases operation and begins demolition.<ref>{{cite web |title=Funan DigitaLife Mall\u2019s last day of trading planned for June 30 |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/funan-digitalife-malls-last-day-trading-planned-jun-30 |website=Today |access-date=29 September 2019 |date=11 December 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Ministry of Defence (Singapore)|MINDEF]] announced that pre-enlistees entering [[National service in Singapore|National Service]] from 2017 can choose vocations (which is later revealed as 33 vocations), subject to operational needs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pre-enlistees entering national service from 2017 can indicate vocation of choice: Ng Eng Hen|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/pre-enlistees-entering-national-service-from-2017-can-indicate-vocation-of-choice-ng-eng|website=The Straits Times|access-date=2 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NS pre-enlistees can pick from 33 vocations|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/ns-pre-enlistees-can-pick-from-33-vocations|website=The Straits Times|access-date=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===July===\n* 5 July \u2013 [[FactWire]] reports that several [[Kawasaki Heavy Industries & CSR Qingdao Sifang C151A|C151A]] trains were being secretly recalled.<ref>{{cite web|title=35 SMRT trains recalled by China manufacturer due to defects: report|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/35-smrt-trains-recalled-by-china-manufacturer-due-100717823.html|publisher=Yahoo|accessdate=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n* 7 July \u2013 A robbery occurs at a [[Standard Chartered]] branch in Holland Village.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lee |first1=Min Kok |last2=Cheong |first2=Danson |last3=Menon |first3=Malavika |title=Police officers searching for suspect after robbery at Standard Chartered bank in Holland Village |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/courts-crime/police-officers-seen-