{"title_page": "Charles Tolle", "text_new": "{{short description|French Paralympic athlete}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[para athletics]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{FRA}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1996 Summer Paralympics|1996 Atlanta]] | [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 4x400 metre relay T52-53|4x400 metre relay - T52-53]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 4x400 metre relay T54|4x400 metre relay - T54]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 400 metres T53|400 metres - T53]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''Charles Tolle''' is a [[paralympic]] [[track and field|athlete]] from [[France]] competing mainly in category T53 wheelchair racing events.\n\nCharles has competed in 3 Paralympics, winning 3 medals in two games.  He first competed in the [[1996 Summer Paralympics]] where he competed in the 200m and 400m, and won a gold medal as part of the French 4 \u00d7 400 m relay team.  In the [[2000 Summer Paralympics]] he won a bronze in the individual 400m as well as helping the French relay team defend there Gold medal and competing in the 200m and marathon.  His third appearance proved to be his least successful, competing in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] he competed in the 200m, 400m and 800m without winning a medal.\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?sport=all&games=all&Medal=all&npc=all&name=Tolle&fname=Charles&gender=all |title=profile on paralympic.org |website=paralympic.org}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|charles-tolle}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tolle, Charles}}\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1992 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1996 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2000 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1996 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2000 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{France-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French Paralympic athlete}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalSport | [[Track and field]] (athletics)}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{FRA}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1996 Summer Paralympics|1996 Atlanta]] | [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 4x400 metre relay T52-53|4x400 metre relay - T52-53]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 4x400 metre relay T54|4x400 metre relay - T54]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's 400 metres T53|400 metres - T53]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''Charles Tolle''' is a [[paralympic]] [[track and field|athlete]] from [[France]] competing mainly in category T53 wheelchair racing events.\n\nCharles has competed in 3 Paralympics, winning 3 medals in two games.  He first competed in the [[1996 Summer Paralympics]] where he competed in the 200m and 400m, and won a gold medal as part of the French 4 \u00d7 400 m relay team.  In the [[2000 Summer Paralympics]] he won a bronze in the individual 400m as well as helping the French relay team defend there Gold medal and competing in the 200m and marathon.  His third appearance proved to be his least successful, competing in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] he competed in the 200m, 400m and 800m without winning a medal.\n<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?sport=all&games=all&Medal=all&npc=all&name=Tolle&fname=Charles&gender=all profile on paralympic.org]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tolle, Charles}}\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1992 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1996 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2000 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1996 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2000 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{France-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "add Paralympics link, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Tolle"}
{"title_page": "Most Eligible Bachelor (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Most Eligible Bachelor\n| image = Most Eligible Bachelor Poster.jpeg\n| caption = First Look Poster\n| director = [[Bhaskar (director)|Bhaskar]]\n| producer = Bunny Vas<br />[[Vasu Varma]] <br />[[Allu Aravind]](Presenter) \n| writer = Bhaskar\n| starring = [[Akhil Akkineni]]<br />[[Pooja Hegde]] <br/>[[Murali Sharma]]\n| music = [[Gopi Sundar]]\n| cinematography = Pradeesh Varma\n| editing =  [[Marthand K. Venkatesh]] \n| studio = [[Geetha Arts|GA2 Pictures]]\n| released =\n| runtime = \n| country = India\n| language = Telugu\n| budget = \n| gross = \n}}\n\n'''''Most Eligible Bachelor''''' is an upcoming [[India]]n [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film written and directed by [[Bhaskar (director)|Bhaskar]] and produced by Bunny Vas and [[Vasu Varma]] on [[Geetha Arts|GA2 Pictures]] featuring [[Akhil Akkineni]], [[Pooja Hegde]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://telugu.news18.com/news/movies/akhil-akkineni-new-title-most-eligible-bachelor-and-akhil-first-look-go-viral-ta-448658.html |title=\u0c28\u0c21\u0c3f\u0c30\u0c4b\u0c21\u0c4d\u0c21\u0c41\u0c2a\u0c48 \u0c1a\u0c46\u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c2a\u0c41\u0c32\u0c41 \u0c32\u0c47\u0c15\u0c41\u0c02\u0c21\u0c3e\u0c28\u0c47 \u0c05\u0c15\u0c4d\u0c15\u0c3f\u0c28\u0c47\u0c28\u0c3f \u0c35\u0c3e\u0c30\u0c41\u0c38\u0c41\u0c21\u0c41.. \u0c05\u0c2f\u0c4d\u0c2f\u0c47 \u0c07\u0c26\u0c47\u0c02 \u0c17\u0c24\u0c3f.. |date=2020-02-08 |website=News18 Telugu |publisher=[[CNN-News18]] |location=India |access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> The music was composed by [[Gopi Sundar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/akhils-4th-film-with-bommarillu-bhaskar-launched/articleshow/69478015.cms|title=Akhil's 4th film with Bommarillu Bhaskar launched - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The film was scheduled to release in April 2020,<ref name=\"FSP\">{{cite web|author=Geetha ArtsVerified account |url=https://twitter.com/GeethaArts/status/1226121064075292672?s=19 |title=Geetha Arts on Twitter: \"Journey of our #MostEligibleBachelor starts now with this step |publisher=Twitter.com |date=2009-11-26 |accessdate=2020-02-08}}</ref> but was postponed due to the [[2019&ndash;20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>https://www.tollywood.net/story-line-of-akhils-meb-revealed/</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nIn February 2019, story discussions took place between [[Akhil Akkineni]] and director [[Bhaskar (director)|Bhaskar]] with [[Geetha Arts|GA2 Pictures]]'s Bunny Vas attached to produce the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/akhils-next-with-bommarillu-bhaskar-set-to-kick-off-from-summer/articleshow/68073881.cms|title=Akhil's next with Bommarillu Bhaskar set to kick-off from summer - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n=== Muhurtham (Launch) ===\nOn 24 May 2019 movie got officially launched at Filmnagar temple with Pooja. Akhil's parents [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]], [[Amala Akkineni]] along with film crew joined the occasion. It was also revealed director [[Vasu Varma]] is co producing along with Bunny Vas<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/akhil-akkinenis-will-be-working-with-bommarillu-bhaskar-for-his-next-420049.htm|title=Akhil Akkineni's will be working with Bommarillu Bhaskar for his next|first1=Bommarillu Bhaskar In com Staff-|last1=May 24|first2=2019 09:13 Pm|last2=Ist|website=in.com}}</ref>.\n\n=== Casting ===\nThe film crew auditioned over 100 actresses and models for leading actress<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/akhil-team-thumb-down-100-divas-552013|title=Akhil & team thumb down 100 divas?|first=B. V. S.|last=Prakash|website=The Hans India|date=2019-08-04}}</ref>. They finalised [[Pooja Hegde]] as the lead in August 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/movies/pooja-hegde-roped-in-to-romance-akhil-akkineni-in-bommarillu-bhaskars-next-2288219.html|title=Pooja Hegde Roped in to Romance Akhil Akkineni in Bommarillu Bhaskar's Next|website=www.news18.com}}</ref>.\n=== Filming ===\nThe filming is scheduled for July 2019. However with delay in finilising female lead, the filming is delayed. The filming started early September with all the lead actors filmed. <ref>{{Cite tweet|user=GeethaArts|number=1175040498156720129|title=Welcoming @hegdepooja on her Day 1 shoot of #Akhil4 today|author=Geetha Arts|date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Akhil Akkineni]] as Nagaraju Pandey\n* [[Pooja Hegde]] as Vibha\n* [[Aamani]]<ref name=\"Cast\" >{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/akhil-akkineni-bommarillu-bhaskar-film-titled-most-eligible-bachelor-title-poster-unveiled/amp_articleshow/73936428.cms |title=Akhil Akkineni, Bommarillu Bhaskar film titled Most Eligible Bachelor; title poster unveiled &#124; Telugu Movie News - Times of India |publisher=M.timesofindia.com |date=2020-02-04 |accessdate=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n* [[Murali Sharma]] <ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Vennela Kishore]] <ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Jayaprakash]] <ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Pragathi]] <ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Amit Tiwari]]<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Eesha Rebba]]<ref>{{cite web|author=akhil pooja hegde |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/amp/entertainment/tollywood/040220/akhils-the-most-eligible-bachelor.html |title=Akhil\u2019s the Most Eligible Bachelor |publisher=Deccanchronicle.com |date=2020-02-04 |accessdate=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n* Getup Srinu<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Sudigali Sudheer]]<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* Abhay<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Most Eligible Bachelor \n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Gopi Sundar]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| venue        = \n|